# AIDLC control plane — workspace-root .gitignore
#
# This folder is the control plane and SHOULD be its own git repo: it versions
# backlog/, .claude/aidlc.config.json, epic coordination files and cross-repo
# ADRs, and it is the branch/merge target for `control-plane`-routed work items.
#
# Product repos are SEPARATE git repos living in subfolders here, and must never
# be tracked from this repo. An untracked nested repo picked up by `git add -A`
# is staged as a mode-160000 gitlink — a submodule with no .gitmodules entry —
# which clones as an empty directory and reports no error.

# --- product repo checkouts (one line per repos[] entry) ---
# Managed block: /aidlc:init writes these at scaffold time and /aidlc:repo add
# appends to it. Use explicit paths, never a blanket `*/` — root-level folders
# that are NOT repos (docs/, scripts/) must stay tracked.
# AIDLC:REPOS
# AIDLC:REPOS-END

# --- local / machine-specific ---
.claude/settings.local.json

# --- ephemeral control-plane state (pids, absolute paths, logs) ---
.aidlc/sprint-*.json
.aidlc/staged-claude/
.aidlc/logs/

# --- tooling ---
node_modules/
*.log

# Durable state stays TRACKED on purpose: backlog/, .aidlc/runs/,
# .aidlc/extensions.json, .claude/aidlc.config.json.
